		<div id="content">
			<div id="column1" class="column">
				<span id="tagline">Capture your ideas, refine them later, publish when ready</span>
				
				<p>Ever think of something for your Twitter that you don't want to post right away? Birdhouse is the perfect place to put it.</p>
				<p>Birdhouse won't replace your favorite iPhone Twitter client, it'll add to it. Put Birdhouse right next to your Twitter client and use them together.</p>
				
				<h3 id="features">Features</h3>
				<ul>
					<li>Quickly jot down your ideas, just like in Notes.</li>
					<li>Count down to 140 characters, just like in Twitter.</li>
					<li>Save as many as you want, revisit them later.</li>
					<li>Capture your ideas offline, even in Airplane mode.</li>
					<li>Rate drafts with stars and sort by best or by newest.</li>
					<li>Manage and publish from multiple Twitter accounts.</li>
					<li>Unpublish the bad ones just as easily.</li>
					<li>Back everything up through email.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			
